OL,6,FImran, of Salford, claimed he had been
OL,7,F"threatened and coerced" by his
OL,8,Fflatmate. He has since pleaded guilty
OL,9,Fto an offence of theft and two
OL,10,Foffences of fraud by false
OL,11,Frepresentation.
OL,13,FProsecuting, Evita Perkone said Imran
OL,14,Fwas employed as a customer advisor at
OL,15,FBoots since 2023, previously working
OL,16,Fin Brighton before moving to
OL,17,FManchester and working at the store in
OL,18,Fthe Trafford Centre.
