OL,3,CBoots worker gave himself points and
OL,4,Cused #3,000 of bogus vouchers
OL,6,F"An example of the theft is shown on
OL,7,FCCTV on February 11, 2025, wherein the
OL,8,Fdefendant retrieved cash from the till
OL,9,Fand placed it into his waistband,"
OL,10,Fsaid Ms Perkone.
OL,12,FHe was ultimately arrested in March
OL,13,F2025 and has since pleaded guilty to
OL,14,Fthe offences.JThe total value of the
OL,15,Fmonies taken was #7,683.
OL,17,FAndrew Sinker, defending, said that
OL,18,FImran was living in a flat in Salford
OL,19,Fat the time, and was being "threatened
OL,20,Fby an Afghan male", who demanded the
OL,21,Fmoney from him.
